Version:
         3dRNAscore-1.0

Install:
         Step 1.  Just type 'make' in the command line.
                  A binary executable file named '3dRNAscore' would be created in the 'bin' directory.
         Step 2.  Set the 'RNAscore' environment to the path of the 3dRNAscore directory.

Caution: 
         It's better to check if the pdb files lack some atoms. We have provided a perl 
         script named 'format.pl' in the 'lib' directory to help to check missing atoms. 
         Just type './format.pl -check filename'. 

Usage: 
         1   ./3dRNAscore {-s}|{--score} <pdb_file> [<parameter_file>]
               # score a single RNA named '<pdb_file>'.
                 We've provided a sample parameter file in the 'lib' directory. The user 
                 can control the parameters through the parameter file. 
         2   ./3dRNAscore {-s:l}|{--score:list} <list_file> [<parameter_file>]
               # score a list of RNA whose name were listed in the file '<parameter_file>'
         3   ./3dRNAscore {-h}|{--help}
               # help information
         4   ./3dRNAscore {-v}|{--version}
               # version information

Please feel free to contact the 3dRNAscore team if you have any question!
